event.title: 1853, a railroad survey by B. Dornblazer determined

data.event: In 1853, a railroad survey by B. Dornblazer determined a course through present-day Lena.
During the summer of 1853, lots sold rapidly, commanding prices varying from $50 to $150 each.

event.title: New Year's Day 1854, track was laid

data.event: On New Year's Day 1854, track was laid, and railway cars began running between Freeport and Warren.
